# Binary media — must be served from Supabase Storage or CDN, not committed to git.
# The existing committed files (public/hvac/audio, public/videos, public/audio) need
# to be removed with: git rm -r --cached public/hvac/audio public/hvac/videos public/audio public/videos
# after confirming all files are uploaded to the CDN. These rules prevent new ones being added.
public/hvac/audio/*.mp3
public/hvac/videos/*.mp4
public/audio/*.mp3
public/audio/*.wav
# public/videos/*.mp4 — hero MP4s are committed directly for Netlify
